# Supabase Auth — OAuth 2.1 Server Reference

**Status**: Public beta (November 2025). Available on Pro plan and above.

Supabase can now act as an OAuth 2.1 identity provider — meaning your Rocket app
can issue tokens to third-party apps, AI agents, or CLI tools, with full RLS enforcement.

---

## What This Enables

```
Without OAuth 2.1 server:
  Only your app can access your Supabase data (via anon/service_role key)

With OAuth 2.1 server:
  → "Sign in with [Your App]" button on other apps
  → AI agents (Claude, Cursor plugins) authenticate as real users
  → Third-party developers build integrations with scoped access
  → CLI tools authenticate users via browser OAuth flow
  → MCP servers authenticate with user-level RLS enforcement
```

---

## Enable the OAuth 2.1 Server

### Step 1 — Switch to asymmetric JWT signing (required for OIDC)
```
Dashboard → Auth → JWT → Signing Algorithm
Switch from: HS256 (symmetric — shared secret)
Switch to:   RS256 or ES256 (asymmetric — public/private key pair)

WARNING: Changing JWT signing algorithm invalidates ALL existing sessions.
All users will be logged out. Do this before you have users, or schedule maintenance.
```

### Step 2 — Enable the OAuth 2.1 server
```
Dashboard → Auth → OAuth Providers (new section, only visible after asymmetric JWT)
→ Enable OAuth 2.1 Server
→ Configure your authorization server metadata URL:
  https://[PROJECT_REF].supabase.co/auth/v1/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server
```

### Step 3 — Register an OAuth client application
```
Dashboard → Auth → OAuth Providers → Register Client Application
  Name: "My CLI Tool" / "Claude Integration" / "[App Name]"
  Redirect URIs: https://yourapp.com/callback (or your tool's callback)
  Allowed scopes: openid profile email (standard) + any custom scopes
  Grant types: authorization_code (for user auth) or client_credentials (for machine auth)

Returns: Client ID and Client Secret — store these securely
```

